The paper discusses the modeling of user request patterns and caching for Video on Demand (VoD) services with recommendation systems. This involves understanding the time-correlation in user requests and determining which contents to cache on servers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of recommendation-based pre-fetching, which involves data mining and machine learning techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. The paper proposes a Markovian request model, which involves probabilistic modeling, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. The paper also discusses Quality of Service (QoS) requirements and resource allocation, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the consistency of the proposed model with existing empirical studies, which involves statistical analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category.
